---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout>
	<main class="container">
        <header class="hero">
            <div class="badge">Technical Assignment</div>
            <h1>Zephyr Cloud <span class="text-gradient">Feedback</span></h1>
            <p class="subtitle">Astro project deployment evaluation and documentation.</p>
            <div class="actions">
                <a href="https://github.com/nicolasbrandao/zephyr-cloud-feedback" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn btn-secondary">
                    View GitHub Repository
                </a>
            </div>
        </header>

        <section class="content-section">
            <div class="card glass">
                <h2>About This Project</h2>
                <p>
                    This static site was created as part of a technical assignment to evaluate Zephyr Cloud. The objective was to integrate the official <code>zephyr-astro-integration</code>, experience the browser-based authentication, and successfully deploy an Astro project to Zephyr's global edge network.
                </p>
                <p>
                    The site serves a dual purpose: it is both the application being deployed and the documentation of the deployment process itself.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="card glass">
                <h2>How Zephyr Cloud Works</h2>
                <p>Based on my research and experience, here is a breakdown of Zephyr Cloud's deployment model:</p>
                <ul class="feature-list">
                    <li>
                        <strong>Integration Hook:</strong> The Astro integration neatly hooks into Vite's build step, meaning <code>pnpm build</code> is all you need.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Content-Addressed Storage:</strong> Assets are hashed and checked against what's already in the cloud, so only new or modified assets are uploaded, significantly accelerating subsequent builds.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Immutable Snapshots:</strong> Every build creates a permanent, immutable version of the project. There's no overwriting—just new snapshots.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Edge Distribution:</strong> Once the snapshot is uploaded, it's immediately pushed to hundreds of edge locations globally for low latency.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Tags & Routing:</strong> Instead of rebuilding for rollbacks, you simply change a tag (like 'production') to point to a different immutable build. This turns rollbacks into instant, metadata-only operations.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="card glass">
                <h2>My Deployment Experience</h2>
                <div class="feedback-grid">
                    <div class="feedback-item">
                        <h3>Blazing Fast Deployment ⚡</h3>
                        <p>
                            The deployment speed with this setup is absolutely fantastic. Because assets are verified via content-addressed storage, only modified files are uploaded. The time between running the build command in the terminal and having the live URL on the edge network is practically instant, heavily optimizing the development experience and feedback loop.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feedback-item">
                        <h3>What went well</h3>
                        <p>
                            The setup was incredibly smooth. Adding the plugin to <code>astro.config.mjs</code> took seconds. The first-time browser authentication via the CLI was seamless and securely wrote credentials to my local machine. The deployment speed in the terminal was impressively fast, and getting an instant live URL without having to configure a CI pipeline or a complex dashboard project was a great developer experience.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feedback-item">
                        <h3>Generous Free Tier</h3>
                        <p>
                            The availability of a solid free tier for developers is a huge plus. It provides the perfect environment for small teams and independent developers to prototype, evaluate the platform, or host personal projects on Zephyr Cloud without having to worry about upfront costs.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feedback-item">
                        <h3>Agentic Development Ready</h3>
                        <p>
                            The official documentation is thoughtfully designed for modern AI workflows. Providing built-in options to copy content directly as Markdown makes it effortless to feed Zephyr's technical guides straight into AI coding assistants and autonomous agents.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feedback-item">
                        <h3>Future Feature: MCP Server or AI SKILL</h3>
                        <p>
                            To take the AI integration even further, providing an official <strong>MCP (Model Context Protocol) server</strong> or a pre-packaged AI <strong>SKILL</strong> would be an incredible addition. This would allow agents to automatically interact with Zephyr Cloud directly from the user's development environment.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feedback-item">
                        <h3>Future Support for SSR</h3>
                        <p>
                            Currently, the Astro integration primarily supports Static Site Generation (SSG). However, it seems active development is already underway to bring Server-Side Rendering (SSR) capabilities to the platform. Once SSR is fully supported, it will open up even more powerful dynamic architectures for Astro projects on Zephyr Cloud. Additionally, a new project currently requires an initialized git repository with a remote origin for production deployments to work, which enforces good practices but might briefly interrupt a quick prototyping flow.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feedback-item">
                        <h3>Auto-generated URLs Formatting</h3>
                        <p>
                            <strong>Warning:</strong> The auto-generated URLs contain the user's email replaced with hyphens (e.g., <code>gmail-com</code>). This formatting, ending in a common domain extension format, can trigger browser phishing protections or fraud warnings before the user joins the page. Improving this generation format would reduce friction when visiting auto-generated deploy links.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <footer>
            <p>Deployed on <strong>Zephyr Cloud</strong></p>
        </footer>
	</main>
</Layout>

<style>
    .container {
        max-width: 900px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 4rem 2rem;
    }

    .hero {
        text-align: center;
        margin-bottom: 5rem;
        animation: fadeUp 0.8s ease-out;
    }

    .badge {
        display: inline-block;
        padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem;
        background-color: rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.1);
        color: var(--accent);
        border: 1px solid rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.2);
        border-radius: 999px;
        font-size: 0.875rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        letter-spacing: 0.05em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
    }

    h1 {
        font-size: 3.5rem;
        font-weight: 800;
        line-height: 1.1;
        margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
        letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    }

    .text-gradient {
        background: var(--gradient);
        -webkit-background-clip: text;
        -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
        background-clip: text;
    }

    .subtitle {
        font-size: 1.25rem;
        color: var(--muted);
        max-width: 600px;
        margin: 0 auto 2.5rem auto;
    }

    .actions {
        display: flex;
        gap: 1rem;
        justify-content: center;
    }

    .btn {
        display: inline-flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
        padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
        border-radius: 8px;
        font-weight: 500;
        text-decoration: none;
        transition: all 0.2s ease;
    }

    .btn-secondary {
        background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
        color: var(--text);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
    }

    .btn-secondary:hover {
        background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
        border-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);
    }

    .content-section {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 2rem;
    }

    .card {
        padding: 2.5rem;
        border-radius: 16px;
        background-color: var(--card-bg);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        box-shadow: 0 4px 24px -8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
        transition: transform 0.3s ease, border-color 0.3s ease;
        animation: fadeUp 0.8s ease-out backwards;
    }

    .card:nth-child(2) { animation-delay: 0.1s; }
    .card:nth-child(3) { animation-delay: 0.2s; }

    .card:hover {
        transform: translateY(-2px);
        border-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
    }

    .glass {
        backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
        -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
    }

    h2 {
        font-size: 1.75rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        margin: 0 0 1.5rem 0;
        color: #f4f4f5;
    }

    h3 {
        font-size: 1.25rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
        color: #e4e4e7;
    }

    p {
        margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
    }

    p:last-child {
        margin-bottom: 0;
    }

    code {
        background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
        padding: 0.2em 0.4em;
        border-radius: 4px;
        font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, monospace;
        font-size: 0.875em;
        color: #93c5fd;
    }

    .feature-list {
        margin: 0;
        padding-left: 1.25rem;
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 1rem;
    }

    .feature-list li {
        padding-left: 0.5rem;
        color: var(--muted);
    }

    .feature-list strong {
        color: var(--text);
        font-weight: 500;
    }

    .feedback-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        gap: 2rem;
    }

    @media (min-width: 768px) {
        .feedback-grid {
            grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        }
        
        h1 {
            font-size: 4.5rem;
        }
    }

    .feedback-item {
        background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
        padding: 1.5rem;
        border-radius: 12px;
        border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
    }

    .feedback-item p {
        color: var(--muted);
        font-size: 0.95rem;
    }

    footer {
        margin-top: 5rem;
        text-align: center;
        color: var(--muted);
        font-size: 0.875rem;
        padding-top: 2rem;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    }

    @keyframes fadeUp {
        from {
            opacity: 0;
            transform: translateY(20px);
        }
        to {
            opacity: 1;
            transform: translateY(0);
        }
    }
</style>
